ten years running.

02:53.239 --> 02:54.689
I know but I've got a feeling.

02:54.706 --> 02:56.707
You know, lucky 11?

02:56.775 --> 02:58.726
We can't lose
this time, Dr. Crane.

02:58.727 --> 03:00.295
We're pulling out
all the stops.

03:00.296 --> 03:02.397
We've got, a two
for one special,

03:02.464 --> 03:05.700
we've got balloons,
we've got a live Irish band,

03:05.767 --> 03:09.603
we've got Mr. Peterson
mixing up some green beer.

03:09.671 --> 03:12.140
Oh, hey, how's that
beer coming, Norm?

03:12.208 --> 03:14.975
You want it fast or
you want it good?

03:15.043 --> 03:17.812
Come on, you've been working
on it for three hours.

03:17.880 --> 03:21.049
And I'm prepared to work on it
all night long, Sam,

03:21.116 --> 03:23.584
because damn it, I care.

03:23.652 --> 03:25.203
Normie, watch this.

03:25.271 --> 03:27.872
(knocking)
Hey, Carla. You-you through in there?

03:27.940 --> 03:29.750
CARLA:
Hold your horses. I'm coming.

03:36.815 --> 03:38.850
Shut up, everybody.

03:38.851 --> 03:39.967
Hey, look, everybody.

03:39.968 --> 03:43.437
It's our little
leprechaun, Brill O'Head.

03:43.505 --> 03:48.042
Keep talking, Clavin, you'll
lose your left Blarney Stone.

03:48.110 --> 03:50.161
This outfit is ridiculous.

03:50.229 --> 03:51.829
I mean, I want to beat Gary

03:51.897 --> 03:55.066
as much as the next guy,
but I'm not wearing this, okay?

03:55.134 --> 03:56.668
I think it kind of looks nice.

03:56.735 --> 03:59.287
Yeah, I think it
looks kind of sexy. That's it.

04:01.490 --> 04:03.124
Please, please.

04:03.191 --> 04:05.877
Hey, everybody,
I've got great news.

04:05.878 --> 04:07.746
I applied to the Boston
League of Businesswomen,

04:07.747 --> 04:09.330
and they might let me join.

04:09.398 --> 04:10.565
Oh, who are they?

04:10.633 --> 04:13.033
Oh, it's this very
prestigious organization

04:13.034 --> 04:15.069
that helps raise the stature
of women in society...

04:15.070 --> 04:17.654
and that kind of crap.

04:17.723 --> 04:19.053
Sam, I need a couple hours

04:19.053 --> 04:21.142
off tomorrow because
they want to interview me.

04:21.142 --> 04:23.344
Honey, it's the
busiest day of my year.

04:23.345 --> 04:24.612
What difference does it make?

04:24.613 --> 04:25.980
She doesn't do anything anyway.

04:25.981 --> 04:28.283
You know what?

04:28.284 --> 04:29.917
Why don't you take
the whole day off?

04:29.918 --> 04:32.987
You're a peach.

04:33.054 --> 04:34.222
Hi, everybody.

04:34.290 --> 04:35.723
(booing)

04:35.791 --> 04:38.843
What the hell do you
want here, Gary?

04:38.844 --> 04:40.928
Well, you know, in the spirit
of Saint Patrick's Day,

04:40.929 --> 04:43.230
I thought I'd come over here and
give you guys a chance

04:43.231 --> 04:44.491
to call off our little bet

04:44.492 --> 04:46.100
and, uh, save yourselves
the supreme humiliation.

04:46.101 --> 04:48.119
I'll tell you what, Gary,

04:48.186 --> 04:50.388
we're gonna win this
lousy bet this year.

04:50.389 --> 04:52.506
Not only that, we're gonna make
ten times more money than you.

04:52.507 --> 04:54.342
And you know why?
Because we've got a strategy.

04:54.343 --> 04:56.928
Well, you know, if you're so
sure of yourself, Malone,

04:56.929 --> 04:58.796
maybe you'd like to raise
the stakes a little bit

04:58.797 --> 05:00.698
and make it more interesting
than the usual 100 bucks?

05:00.699 --> 05:02.366
What you got in mind?

05:02.367 --> 05:04.752
Oh, just a little something
that the loser has to do.

05:04.753 --> 05:06.487
What are you doing?

05:08.723 --> 05:11.325
Oh, I don't know, Gary, uh...

05:11.326 --> 05:14.061
Well, okay well,
if you're going to be chicken about it.

05:14.062 --> 05:16.313
Oh, I'm not being chicken,
because we're gonna win anyway.

05:16.314 --> 05:19.133
So, we've got a deal?

05:19.134 --> 05:20.518
Uh, all right. All right.
Yeah, yeah.

05:20.519 --> 05:23.321
But wait a minute, what is the,
uh, what are the ground rules?

05:23.322 --> 05:25.540
Malone, there's only
one rule, no rules.

05:25.607 --> 05:27.859
Just the way I like it.
Great.

05:27.927 --> 05:29.877
May the best man win.

05:29.945 --> 05:32.447
Sam, may I have
a word with you? Yeah.

05:32.448 --> 05:34.114
I strongly urge you
to reconsider.

05:34.115 --> 05:36.617
Listen, why do you think Gary's
so willing to up the stakes?

05:36.618 --> 05:39.454
I mean, it stands to
reason that he thinks he's going to win.

05:39.455 --> 05:40.488
No, no, he's bluffing.

05:40.489 --> 05:41.809
What makes you think that?

05:41.857 --> 05:44.058
Well he-he's beaten us
ten times in a row.

05:44.125 --> 05:46.728
And not one of those times
has he raised the stakes.

05:46.795 --> 05:49.196
He's running scared.

05:49.264 --> 05:53.267
Well, don't I feel stupid.

05:53.335 --> 05:57.004
All those degrees really don't
do much, do they, Doctor?

06:02.310 --> 06:03.461
Sammy, what's up?

06:03.462 --> 06:05.630
I thought you wanted to get
an early jump on Gary.

06:05.631 --> 06:07.498
Yeah, I did. That's
why I'm here at 9:00.

06:07.499 --> 06:08.549
9:01, Sam.

06:08.567 --> 06:10.168
Some of us were
here at 9:00.

06:10.236 --> 06:12.137
Hey, relax, will you.
It's in the bag.

06:12.204 --> 06:14.922
I fixed it so Gary
can't ever win.

06:14.990 --> 06:16.657
Yeah?
Yeah? What'd you do?

06:16.658 --> 06:18.426
Yeah, you're gonna love this.
You know that-that sign

06:18.427 --> 06:19.727
he's got outside
his window there,

06:19.728 --> 06:21.195
"50 cent beer,
Saint Patrick's Day Special?"

06:21.196 --> 06:23.030
CARLA:
Yeah. Yeah, well I added a zero.

06:23.031 --> 06:25.433
I mean who's going to pay
$5 for a beer, huh?

06:25.500 --> 06:27.268
Good one, Sam.
Yeah.

06:27.336 --> 06:29.270
Sometimes I scare myself.

06:29.338 --> 06:31.072
It's 9:02, Sam. Let's go.

06:31.139 --> 06:33.191
All right. Sorry.

06:33.192 --> 06:34.175
$5 beer.

06:34.176 --> 06:36.244
(laughing)

06:36.311 --> 06:37.778
Yeah, let's see him top that.

06:37.846 --> 06:40.481
(gasps)

06:42.767 --> 06:47.304
See now, that,
that's not right.

06:47.372 --> 06:49.890
Gary did it to us again.

06:49.958 --> 06:53.628
Walled off from the keg.

06:53.695 --> 06:56.397
I want him dead, Sam.

06:56.465 --> 06:57.665
His family, dead.

06:57.733 --> 06:59.467
His friends, dead!

06:59.534 --> 07:02.086
SAM:
Oh, now see, this, this is,

07:02.154 --> 07:04.322
this is the lowest thing
a person can do.

07:04.389 --> 07:05.589
This is pure evil.

07:05.657 --> 07:06.707
Yeah.

07:06.725 --> 07:08.876
Why can't we think like that?

07:08.943 --> 07:10.578
Tell me about it.

07:10.646 --> 07:13.931
I thought you left Woody here to
guard against things like this.

07:13.999 --> 07:16.469
WOODY (voice echoing):
Sorry, Sam. I fell asleep.

07:19.337 --> 07:23.875
They walled Woody in the bar.

07:25.443 --> 07:27.728
Woody, you all right in there?

07:27.796 --> 07:30.664
Well, I'm feeling
light-headed and woozy, Sam.

07:30.732 --> 07:32.450
That's the way I want to feel.

07:32.518 --> 07:34.385
Somebody tear this thing down!

07:38.873 --> 07:42.143
New Armani, new hair.

07:42.211 --> 07:45.813
Am I ready for the Boston League
of Businesswomen or what?

07:45.880 --> 07:49.450
I just have to get my resume
and then I'm on my way.

07:55.607 --> 07:58.109
Is this in any way my fault?

07:58.177 --> 07:59.777
No, sweetheart.

07:59.845 --> 08:02.296
Okay then wish me luck.
Bye-bye.

08:05.667 --> 08:08.352
Yep. Crisis solved.

08:08.420 --> 08:10.004
Where'd you get the beer?

08:10.071 --> 08:13.201
I've got a few squirrelled away
around the bar for emergencies.

08:13.202 --> 08:16.110
I always kind of figured it
would be a nuclear thing,

08:16.111 --> 08:18.178
but I think this qualifies.

08:22.417 --> 08:24.752
Where would you like us
to set up, Mr. Malone?

08:24.820 --> 08:26.320
Oh, hi. fellows.

08:26.388 --> 08:28.556
Uh... uh, yeah, why not?

08:28.557 --> 08:29.990
I'll tell you what,
right over there.

08:29.991 --> 08:31.124
Thank you very much...

08:31.125 --> 08:32.193
Hey, come on, Norm, Carla,

08:32.193 --> 08:33.660
listen we can still win
this thing, right?

08:33.662 --> 08:35.563
We, we've got
the green beer, we've got the band.

08:35.563 --> 08:37.798
All we've got to do is
get rid of this wall somehow

08:37.799 --> 08:39.534
