14:43.514 --> 14:45.982
You know, my underwear's
a little tight.

14:46.051 --> 14:48.952
It's funny, mine's
a little loose.

14:49.020 --> 14:50.454
(both scream)

14:52.730 --> 14:55.509
HARRY:
Let me get this straight.

14:55.510 --> 14:57.944
Over the years, Gary has put
sheep in your office,

14:57.945 --> 15:00.481
had exterminators shut you down,

15:00.482 --> 15:02.083
and then yesterday
he built a brick wall

15:02.084 --> 15:04.685
around the bar
and had you perform naked?

15:04.752 --> 15:07.404
Listen, we need your help bad.

15:07.472 --> 15:09.774
I'm sorry, Sam,
I'm not interested.

15:09.825 --> 15:11.609
Oh, all right, fine.
Fine, Harr.

15:11.676 --> 15:12.726
What is your price?

15:12.744 --> 15:14.374
No, I don't want
your money, Sam.

15:14.379 --> 15:16.647
Besides, if I did,
I could take it.

15:16.698 --> 15:18.966
I kind of like you guys.

15:19.001 --> 15:22.603
So let me give you a piece of
advice: stop trying to top Gary.

15:22.604 --> 15:23.838
You're never gonna beat him.

15:23.839 --> 15:26.273
Face it.
You're a bunch of losers.

15:28.176 --> 15:29.616
It's nothing to be ashamed of.

15:29.617 --> 15:30.794
It's your nature you know?

15:30.795 --> 15:32.263
It's the way God made you.

15:32.264 --> 15:33.480
You're part of his master plan.

15:33.481 --> 15:34.948
If it weren't for you guys,

15:35.016 --> 15:37.417
how would we know
who the winners were?

15:39.221 --> 15:41.422
No, we're not losers.

15:41.489 --> 15:43.179
All right, fine,
have it your way.

15:43.224 --> 15:44.858
Woody, give me a beer, huh?

15:44.977 --> 15:46.360
Sure.

15:46.361 --> 15:48.128
CLIFF: Yeah, but don't
forget to charge him, Woody.

15:48.129 --> 15:49.329
Get some money out of him.

15:49.330 --> 15:50.464
Yeah, all right, all right.

15:50.465 --> 15:51.735
What do I owe you, Woody?

15:51.817 --> 15:53.466
Well, that'll be two dollars.

15:53.467 --> 15:54.869
Hey, you know, I got
a lot of change here.

15:54.870 --> 15:56.738
Will you take all this
and give me a 20?

15:56.739 --> 15:58.522
Well, you know,

15:58.573 --> 15:59.873
be careful of that Woody.

15:59.941 --> 16:00.991
I think he's pulling

16:00.992 --> 16:02.376
his flimflam
short change thing here.

16:02.377 --> 16:03.377
Really?

16:03.378 --> 16:04.545
Yeah, yeah.
Count the money.

16:04.546 --> 16:07.948
Oh... oh, this isn't right.

16:08.000 --> 16:09.166
Aha. Yeah, see?

16:09.233 --> 16:10.501
You gave me too much.

16:10.502 --> 16:11.569
Huh?

16:11.570 --> 16:12.736
That's your tip, Woody.

16:12.754 --> 16:14.955
Oh, no, I'm not falling
for that.

16:15.022 --> 16:17.991
I'll just keep
the two dollars for the beer.

16:18.060 --> 16:20.478
Yeah. See, Harry?

16:20.545 --> 16:22.813
We're not as stupid
as you think we are.

16:22.881 --> 16:23.961
No, I guess you're not.

16:24.016 --> 16:25.883
Here's your wallet, Cliff.

16:28.720 --> 16:32.422
Wow, he's good.
Very good.

16:32.491 --> 16:34.191
Aw, who are we kidding,
you guys?

16:34.258 --> 16:35.759
We might as well just quit.

16:35.777 --> 16:38.979
Hey, wait, wait a minute.
What are you saying?

16:39.046 --> 16:41.047
You mean after
Gary's done to us,

16:41.048 --> 16:42.816
you're just gonna roll over
and die?

16:42.817 --> 16:44.017
You're gonna walk away?

16:44.018 --> 16:45.536
You're gonna be a quitter, Sam?

16:45.537 --> 16:47.621
Yeah, Carla, that's exactly what
I'm gonna do.

16:47.622 --> 16:49.824
I'm gonna quit!
I'm tired of losing to the guy.

16:49.825 --> 16:51.124
Tomorrow I'm gonna go
over there.

16:51.125 --> 16:53.727
I'm gonna make my peace with him
once and for all.

16:53.795 --> 16:55.229
Well, go.

16:55.230 --> 16:57.097
But I'm not lettin' him
off the hook.

16:57.098 --> 16:58.332
This is personal now.

16:58.399 --> 17:00.334
And I don't know what,
I don't know,

17:00.401 --> 17:02.802
but I swear I am gonna do
something to that guy.

17:02.803 --> 17:04.238
Look, Carla,
we're willing to give in.

17:04.239 --> 17:05.571
You should, too.

17:05.573 --> 17:07.608
It's not like you had
to dance naked over there.

17:07.608 --> 17:10.577
No, but I had to look at it
on videotape.

17:10.612 --> 17:14.515
Gary's selling videotapes?

17:14.566 --> 17:17.935
No, He's giving them away
with every five-dollar beer.

17:22.323 --> 17:25.125
Can you believe it?
The League rejected me.

17:25.193 --> 17:26.292
Why?

17:26.361 --> 17:28.531
Because they said I was
too self-involved

17:28.531 --> 17:30.163
and that I wasn't
community-minded enough.

17:30.164 --> 17:32.633
So now I have to spend
the next six months

17:32.701 --> 17:35.769
doing community
service. Yawn.

17:35.887 --> 17:37.754
Woody, get me a charity
on the phone.

17:37.822 --> 17:38.872
Which one?

17:38.889 --> 17:40.490
How the hell do I know?!

17:40.491 --> 17:42.909
Just make sure it's close by.

17:42.910 --> 17:45.596
And I don't want one
that's real depressing.

17:46.964 --> 17:48.665
And no weekends!

17:57.025 --> 17:58.492
(knocking)

18:10.304 --> 18:12.272
(engine starts)

18:19.714 --> 18:21.815
Oh! Oh!

18:25.103 --> 18:26.286
Oh, God! Oh, God!

18:26.354 --> 18:29.589
Oh, God!

18:29.641 --> 18:31.274
Oh, Carla!

18:38.283 --> 18:40.150
(hushed):
Carla!

18:40.151 --> 18:42.803
I just came back from Gary's!

18:42.804 --> 18:44.771
Wha, what were you thinking?!

18:44.839 --> 18:46.373
Are you crazy?!

18:46.374 --> 18:48.275
I really got him good,
didn't I, Sam?

18:48.276 --> 18:49.510
Got him good?

18:49.577 --> 18:51.567
Honey, we're in
serious trouble here!

18:51.613 --> 18:53.847
What are you talking about?

18:53.915 --> 18:55.883
Malone!
You went way too far this time.

18:55.950 --> 18:57.651
You're gonna go to jail
for this!

18:57.669 --> 19:00.337
I swear to God, Gare, we had
nothing to do with this.

19:00.338 --> 19:01.738
Wha-what are you talking about?

19:01.739 --> 19:03.307
Just yesterday, you swore
in front of witnesses that,

19:03.308 --> 19:05.593
that you were gonna ruin me.
You said you'd do anything!

19:05.594 --> 19:07.327
That's true, Sam.
I was there.

19:07.395 --> 19:09.729
What the hell
were you thinking, Malone?

19:09.730 --> 19:11.365
Did you think you were
gonna get away with this?!

19:11.366 --> 19:12.783
Well, forget about it.
I'm gonna call the cops.

19:12.784 --> 19:13.967
The cops?!

19:14.019 --> 19:15.118
Wait a minute!

19:15.119 --> 19:16.753
Putting a rat
in a heating system

19:16.754 --> 19:18.221
isn't even a misdemeanour!

19:18.222 --> 19:21.242
Carla, sweetheart, please,
you're just making things worse.

19:21.243 --> 19:23.076
My, my bar is ruined!

19:23.161 --> 19:25.479
Please, man, don't bring
the cops into this.

19:25.480 --> 19:26.846
Listen, I-I'm begging you.

19:26.847 --> 19:28.348
I'm on my knees here.

19:28.416 --> 19:29.650
No, you're not.

19:32.554 --> 19:33.887
Oh...

19:36.424 --> 19:37.991
Please...

19:38.058 --> 19:40.594
Oh, and this is supposed
to be enough?

19:40.679 --> 19:44.314
Help me out here, will ya?
Come on.

19:44.349 --> 19:46.550
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

19:50.055 --> 19:54.708
Sam! Ha-ha, I gotcha!
That's news.

19:55.493 --> 19:58.045
What's, what's going on here?

19:58.046 --> 19:59.746
You fell for it.
It was a trick.

19:59.814 --> 20:00.948
What is a trick?

20:01.015 --> 20:02.882
I saw your bar being bulldozed!

20:02.901 --> 20:05.168
Somebody bulldozed your bar?

20:05.203 --> 20:06.836
I bulldozed my bar.

20:06.837 --> 20:08.905
You see, I sold my property
to a commercial developer,

20:08.906 --> 20:10.774
and he's going to put a shopping
centre on my old spot.

20:10.775 --> 20:12.376
I'm getting a million bucks
for it.

20:12.377 --> 20:13.643
But the best part is,

20:13.644 --> 20:16.113
you guys have humiliated
yourselves at the feet

20:16.114 --> 20:18.648
of the master one last time.

20:18.667 --> 20:20.534
Yeah, well, the joke's on you.

20:20.601 --> 20:23.436
We happen to need a shopping
centre in this area.

20:23.555 --> 20:25.922
Sam, I hope you don't mind,

20:25.923 --> 20:27.691
but since I don't have
a bar anymore,

20:27.692 --> 20:29.593
I invited the developer
over here to, you know,

20:29.594 --> 20:31.762
help me celebrate.

20:38.510 --> 20:42.689
Sam, I'd like you to
meet your new neighbour,

20:42.690 --> 20:44.458
Rutherford Cunningham.

20:44.459 --> 20:45.993
Real nice place you have here.

20:45.994 --> 20:48.695
Nice to meet you.

20:48.763 --> 20:50.163
Sam, is it?

20:50.282 --> 20:52.032
Yeah.

20:52.083 --> 20:53.867
A bottle of your
finest champagne.

20:53.952 --> 20:56.269
(phone rings)
WOODY: Cheers.

20:56.271 --> 20:58.622
Oh, Gary, uh, phone for you,
the bank.

20:58.623 --> 21:01.441
Oh, yeah. Sam, do you mind
if I take that in your office?

21:01.442 --> 21:03.010
It's big business,
that sort of thing.

21:03.011 --> 21:05.128
Sure.

21:05.263 --> 21:08.615
Bank's not used
to million-dollar deposits.

21:08.683 --> 21:11.635
So, Sam!
It's good to see you again.

21:11.702 --> 21:14.954
Now what's that I heard about
the finest champagne?

21:15.022 --> 21:16.690
Did you do this?

21:16.757 --> 21:19.176
Did you, did you destroy
his bar?

21:19.244 --> 21:21.662
No, I didn't.
Gary did.

21:21.729 --> 21:23.963
He's the one hired
the bulldozer.

21:23.964 --> 21:26.166
Me? I'm just an interested
land developer

21:26.167 --> 21:28.602
who's gonna come up a little
short on funds...

21:28.670 --> 21:33.073
say about a million bucks short.

21:33.140 --> 21:37.043
I have the same problem
with a decimal point.

21:37.162 --> 21:39.813
(Gary screams)

21:39.831 --> 21:40.998
Excuse me.

21:41.065 --> 21:44.034
I believe that's the sound
of my check bouncing.

21:45.302 --> 21:47.470
Mr. Cunningham?

21:47.538 --> 21:51.508
Uh, where's,
uh, Mr. Cunningham?

21:51.559 --> 21:52.943
Uh, he left.

21:53.010 --> 21:54.845
Uh, why, Gary?

21:54.979 --> 21:56.830
Uh, no reason.

21:58.218 --> 22:00.233
Oh, man!

22:00.234 --> 22:02.102
Oh, you are terrific!

22:08.109 --> 22:11.260
If you guys ever need any more
help, you just give me a call.

22:11.328 --> 22:12.929
Oh, thank you, Harry.

22:12.997 --> 22:14.397
Ah, don't mention it.

22:14.465 --> 22:17.333
I guess I've always had
a soft spot for you lunkheads.

22:17.369 --> 22:19.619
Hey, how are we ever
gonna pay you back?

22:19.671 --> 22:23.022
Sam, you already have.

22:23.091 --> 22:25.392
Aw, what a guy, huh?

22:25.427 --> 22:26.627
Wonder what he meant by,

22:26.694 --> 22:28.684
we already have
paid him back, though?

22:28.713 --> 22:29.830
Oh, I don't know.

22:29.831 --> 22:32.599
You know, probably that warm
spirit, the camaraderie,

22:32.600 --> 22:33.967
something like that.

22:34.035 --> 22:36.603
Yeah, yeah, he stole
all my money.

